# .aidocs/coding-standards.aidocs - Global Coding Standards

Baseline
- Prefer existing patterns and reuse over new abstractions.
- KISS: keep it stupidly simple.

Data-driven design
- Do not hardcode business rules or tenant/customer-specific fields in general/shared code.
- Prefer generalized domain entities/config (for example tenant/org/workspace plus role/level definitions) as data.
- If you find yourself adding special-case fields or branches for one tenant/customer, issue STOP.

Reuse over reinvent
- Prefer reusing existing project interfaces (CLI/server APIs/tools) over adding new parallel implementations.

Documentation expectations
- Projects should keep backend and frontend documentation concise and actionable.
- When documentation and code disagree, issue STOP before changing either.

Data
- Prefer database designs that follow normal forms unless there is a clear, documented reason to denormalize.

Project portability
- Avoid absolute machine-specific paths in project files.
